      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "THE KID BILLY (1) is in good form at present. Finished fourth at his latest appearance over 1740m at this track, beaten 8 metres. Has the benefit of a good draw. Ideally placed and is sure to prove tough to beat. ROLLONART (6) had to race parked and work so was far disgraced in finishing fifth at this circuit last time out. Looks up to winning this if things go her way. JAY CEE MAXWELL (4) went back last start and couldn't get into the race when 20 metres from the winner in sixth at Young over 1720m. That effort followed a win here two runs ago. Certainly cannot be faulted after that last effort and is good enough to put himself back in the winners' stall. ABOUT MY TIME (8) has trialled three times since his last run so expect he is forward enough to stake a strong claim fresh from a layoff.",
